The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | India drub Nepal 21-0 in hockey
                                                                                                                       7                                      India drub Nepal 21-0 in hockey
                      
	Dhaka: India made a first mark on the medal tally at the 11th South Asian Games when the womens cyclists earned gold in the 30-km road team trial.         
	But the most stunning result for the country on the second day of the meet was the mens hockey teams 21-0 spanking of an inexperienced Nepal on Saturday.         
	Also, the squash duo of Sandip Jangra and Gaurav Nandrajog assured the country of another medal by advancing to the semi-finals. They meet Pakistan in the last-four Sunday.         
	The Indians dominated at the Moulana Bhashani Stadium, where Ajitesh Roy led from the front with five goals versus Nepal.         
	In badminton, the Indian men and women players all got byes into the semis. (PTI)                                                                                                                     
